quizzes.question:
Fill in the blanks:
[!raw!]
ul {
   list-style-{0}: square;
   list-style-{1}: outside;
   list-style-{2}: none;
}

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The list-style Property[/h1]

The [b]list-style[/b] property is a shorthand property for setting list-style-type, list-style-image and list-style-position. It is used to set all of the list properties in one declaration: [code format="css" ]ul {
   [b]list-style[/b]: square outside none;
}[/code]
This would be the same as the longhand version. [code format="css" codeId="555"]ul {
   list-style-type: square;
   list-style-position: outside;
   list-style-image: none;
}[/code]
[b]Result:[/b] [img id="2636" width="100%"]
[note]If one of the property values are missing, the default value for the missing property will be inserted, if any.[/note]
